🟢 Language ➡ C
🟢 Topic ➡ Variable 


📦 Variables in C (Quick Notes)
Variable = Named memory location for storing changeable data.

🛠️ Declaration
 👉 Declare before use with data type and name.
       int age;

🧬 Data Types
Basic: int, float, double, char
Derived: Arrays, Pointers, Structures, Unions, Enums


🚀 Initialization
Can be done during declaration:
    int age = 25;


🌐 Scope
Local: Inside functions → limited access
Global: Outside functions → accessible everywhere


⏳ Lifetime
Local: Exists during function execution
Global: Exists throughout the program


✍️ Naming Rules
Start with letter or _
Use letters, digits, _ only
Case-sensitive


✅ Best Practices
Use descriptive names
Initialize variables
Use const for constants:
const int MAX = 100;


🧠 Memory Storage
Local → Stack
Global/Static/Dynamic → Heap or Data Segment

